===Noun===
'''monkeyshine''' (''plural'' '''[[monkeyshines]]''')
# A [[trick]] or [[prank]] like a monkey's; [[mischief]]; [[buffoonery]]; [[tomfoolery]]; [[monkeyism]]; [[shenanigan]]s.
#: ''I have seen about as many '''monkeyshines''' from you as I will tolerate.''

====Quotations====
* '''1878''': [[w:Augustus Radcliffe Grote|Augustus Radcliffe Grote]], ''[[w:Popular Science|Popular Science Monthly]]'', XIII. 435.
*: You may have noticed barefooted boys cutting up '''monkey-shines''' on trees with entire safety to themselves.

